<br>
Instead of making a fool of yourself asking a stupid question at the fan faire like &quot;will pets be able to hit uber mobs in PoP,&quot; as if the developers had just forgotten about pets (despite the, oh, 3-4 upgrades that have been given to us over the last few months), focus on the issues we really know about, rather than the ones you are just guessing on.<br>
<br>
Issues I know about:<br>
<br>
The pet haste cap...  It makes Muzzle of Mardu and the haste portions of Burnout IV and Burnout V literally useless if you have an epic pet.  Muzzle is still useful if you do not have the epic or BO IV or V.  Source:  Cyricus(has parsed logs).<br>
<br>
Immunities...  pets have new strengths/weaknesses.  Intended or bugged?  Source...  various.  Redorious was first, I believe, and data has been taken.<br>
<br>
Frenzied Burnout...  Worthless because of the haste cap, the 36 second duration, and the broken explosion.  Source: Ylaine (parsed logs) and Cyricus.<br>
<br>
<br>
pets not hitting uber mobs...  ummm  urban myth?  Source:  Someone with other misses on seeing 4 misses in a row and thinking &quot;OH MY GOD MY PET SUXX!!&quot; maybe?<br>
