And since mobs started to drop silly items with Extra Planar Bane on them alot of people suspect PoP will have alot of mobs you need to make baneweapons for.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->True this I had not considered, although this is the first I've heard anyone bring up this issue.  If this was, indeed, his point, I think it would have been cool if he could have asked it using tact as you did explaining it to me, rather than insulting the developers.  <br>
<br>
Although if it was his point you're right, it is an important one.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rhion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Haste caps need to be removed and our pets' levels need to be much higher. End of Story. I don't know how anyone can disagree. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Frankly, if the problem is Mod Rods like you say, I would much rather have them address that rather than upping pet damage so I can feel useful.  Rods already make me feel useful.  If they upped pet levels, it would change approximately nothing as far as boring rod making goes.  The mage high end role shift did not come about because our pets are relatively weaker.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And I see nothing wrong with an epic pet outdamaging a paladin. We are meant to be damage dealers. They are meant to be defenders. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I see nothing wrong with this either, except that right now paladins aren't exactly super defenders.  They're great AE healers, and LoH is awesome, perhaps this is grounds for dealing less damage..  Bumping up pets to be stronger than paladins <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> might</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> balance mages against paladins, but not necessarily everyone else.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Krilen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As the importance and use of rods increases, the other abilities of a magician must decrease in power and usefullness.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Um.. not sure what point you are trying to make here, but this statement is logically false.  <br>
<br>
As the importance and use of rods increases, the other abilities of a magician remain the same.<br>
<br>
I think you maybe forgot the word &quot;relatively.&quot;<br>
