The problem is not if we are under powered, the rub is for us to make ourselves an intricate part of the system, we have to do a duty that , as someone posted here one ... was like getting the golfball for someone else to hit the hole in one. Which is true - we not even the caddy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Having said that, as long as this feature is part of the class, then as long as I play EQ, I will play my class to its best abilities, mostly for my guild mates.......... grudingly and I think this is where most Mages are at <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I would be happy to see a change here in the future to the 'torpor / mass amounts of Mod Rod' combo in PoP, but I doubt it. <br>
